div.p: Query from Decoder, Key/Value from Encoder
Each decoder position has a hidden state that queries encoder information.
Full encoder context all positions available for attention.
Each decoder position scores similarity with all encoder positions.
Probability distribution over encoder positions (rows sum to 1).
Weighted combination of encoder values based on attention weights.

ul.li: K, V come from encoder (source context)

div.p: This allows the decoder to "look up" relevant encoder information while generating each token.
Q = W_Q(decoder_hidden) # From decoder K = W_K(encoder_output) # From encoder V = W_V(encoder_output) # From encoder
scores = Q @ K.T / sqrt(d_k) weights = softmax(scores) context = weights @ V
Decoder: [B, L_dec, D] Q: [B, L_dec, d_k] Encoder: [B, L_enc, D] K: [B, L_enc, d_k] Encoder: [B, L_enc, D] V: [B, L_enc, d_v]
Scores: [B, L_dec, L_enc] (each dec pos each enc pos) Context: [B, L_dec, d_v]
